{
  "stem": "10162.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 78.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The gypsies-- it's that-- some kind of a, a-- national-- racial characteristics or the culture.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They are much more demonstrative, and they scream.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They scream, you know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The, the, the Jews were-- I don't know if it's discipline or what it is, but they just were quiet.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they really screamed terribly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I remember that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyway, this was Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember once weird things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Once, we got some kind of a post card and they said, address it and write something.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everybody got a postcard and a pencil.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, we knew already that we were in a-- we were-- we were in hell and worse.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we all wrote probably the same thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I addressed it to my mother in-- but we said, but there is no one to write it to.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Doesn't matter-- write it as if they were still there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know what purpose that served.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think I addressed it to our old address.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I said, dear Mom and Dad.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I'm here and I'm fine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And don't worry about me or something like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember also once I went over, which I wasn't supposed to, but I went over to this barbed wire, where a soldier was standing on the other side with a gun-- a Wehrmacht soldier.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, they weren't as bad as-- supposedly as the SS, even though I didn't know the difference then.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went over, and I said, may I ask you something in German?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said, well, what?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said, well, do you know where the mothers and the children are?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he said, why?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I said-- I said, because I would like you to-- if you know, I would like you to give a message to my mother.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember I said to him, like, you know, she's very beautiful and my-- the baby and this and that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I gave a little description.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then I'm sure she's very worried about me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And could you please go over, find her, and say that I'm fine?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So anyway, a couple of days later, whenever I saw this soldier again, I said, did you?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he said, I did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I remember that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Any other memories from--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Food?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had to stand on the tzel appel once a day, and they brought some kind of a, you know-- one-- the first person got something in a bowl, some kind of a liquid, inedible liquid.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they would take a few sips and give it to the person behind and behind and behind.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is one-- was one very good way to spread all this infectious-- the typhoid and all this infectious things.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anyway.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the drink was inedible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I decided all the time that whatever they give me, I will drink it and eat it because, that's what I would have to do for my mother.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember the sisters, who I mentioned-- that's why I mentioned them, because they wouldn't.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They would just-- they couldn't take it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They couldn't take a sip of this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's so bad, they couldn't.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they both died right there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were-- before-- they weren't put in a crematorium or anything, but they died, like so many others, because of weakness and starvation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I ate everything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I didn't care what it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I just-- everything I ate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And one very surreal thing I remember that was-- even in Auschwitz, it was surreal.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "One day, they marched us out and we had to sit on this side of the road in like a yoga position.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I don't remember if we got for that day some kind of a clothes, different clothes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We would always get something different to wear.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We had to go-- frequently, we went to the bath, you know, which was a disinfectant in this big room where there were holes in the ceiling.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then we were told that-- well, we always had water coming out of there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But that was the same where the Zyklon gas came from.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And when we were finished, then they would throw us some kind of a clothes from whoever, whoever-- whatever they had.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--disinfected clothes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, what they took off, I guess, from the bodies.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They disinfected everything.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Clean it was.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everything was clean.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was just one of the odd things that-- me and this tall-- a girl who was as tall as I was, we always got the shortest little some kind of a little skirt, you know.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Some short girls got long skirts or whatever.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's how it worked out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So once, they took us to the side of the road.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were supposed to wait for something.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
